cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SD 

This paper involves the use of natural language processing techniques to improve reinforcement learning, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. 

- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category, as the paper specifically mentions the use of neural machine translation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely, as the paper deals with reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possibility, as the paper involves training neural networks to learn associations between natural language and state-action information. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely possibility, but still plausible, as the paper deals with improving agent exploration in unseen environments, which could be relevant to robotics applications. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a less likely possibility, but still possible, as the paper involves implementing and evaluating a modified version of policy shaping.
